al\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">März 15, 2023</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent wide\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104swp1665702587155.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/swp1665702587155.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/swp1665702587155.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"swp1665702587155\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n                              \n Width (xsize)\n   </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Width of the object frame in the layout of a Form or Report, expressed in character cells, excluding the border (if present).\n </p>\n<section class=\"section refsyn\" id=\"swp1665702587155__topic_d100625e1_d100626e1_d100627e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"swp1665702587155__p_d100628e1_d100629e1_d100630e1\">xsize\n                                 <code class=\"ph codeph\">=</code>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">Number</var>\n</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"swp1665702587155__section_y5g_rsh_5wb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1058569e63\">Description</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"swp1665702587155__p_d100634e1_d100635e1_d100636e1\">The size of a character cell is determined by the\n          <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">Font0</span>, as defined in the <span class=\"ph filepath\">usys.ini</span> file. For more\n        information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"api1665703054623.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/api1665703054623.html\" title=\"Specifies the font size that determines the size of the character cell, a unit of measurement that is used by Uniface to control the size and placement of forms and fields in Windows and character mode applications.\">Font0</a>.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"swp1665702587155__section_hqq_ssh_5wb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1058569e88\">Applies To</h2>\n<ul class=\"ul\" id=\"swp1665702587155__ul_gds_tsh_5wb\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"swp1665702587155__li_d40622e1_d40623e1_d40624e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"yth1665702550544.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/yth1665702550544.html\" title=\"A Component Entity is a Development Object that represents data that is owned by a Component. It is part of the Component’s structure and is maintained as part of the Component, although it may reference and inherit from a Modeled Entity.\">Component Entity</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"swp1665702587155__li_d40625e1_d40626e1_d40627e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"zyj1665702550619.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/zyj1665702550619.html\" title=\"A Component Field is a Development Object that represents a unit of data in a Component Entity.\">Component Field</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"swp1665702587155__li_d40628e1_d40629e1_d40630e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"wyt1665702609153.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/wyt1665702609153.html\" title=\"A Label is a Development Object that contains text that appears on a presentation component. Labels have properties, but most cannot be set dynamically.\">Label</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"swp1665702587155__li_d40631e1_d40632e1_d40633e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"eyt1681415255117.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/eyt1681415255117.html\" title=\"An area is a development object that represents an area frame on a Form or Report component. It is used to group objects and style the area it encloses.\">Area</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"swp1665702587155__li_d40634e1_d40635e1_d40636e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"gxr1665702610494.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/gxr1665702610494.html\" title=\"An Area is a Development Object that defines a vertical or horizontal line in the layout of a Form or Report component.\">Line</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"swp1665702587155__li_d40637e1_d40638e1_d40639e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"jxb1665702610180.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/jxb1665702610180.html\" title=\"A Print Header is a Frame in a Form or Report component that is used to print information at the top of each printed page.\">Print Header</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"swp1665702587155__li_d40640e1_d40641e1_d40642e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"jfg1665702610254.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/jfg1665702610254.html\" title=\"A Print Footer is a Frame in a Form or Report component that is used to print information at the bottom of each printed page.\">Print Footer</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"swp1665702587155__li_d40643e1_d40644e1_d40645e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"cjb1665702610334.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/cjb1665702610334.html\" title=\"A Break Frame is a development object in a Form or Report component that is used to display conditional information when a page break is encountered. A component can have multiple break frames.\">Break Frame</a>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"swp1665702587155__section_ayv_tsh_5wb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1058569e179\">Setting in ProcScript</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"swp1665702587155__p_d101009e1_d101010e1_d101011e1\">For component fields in forms, it is possible to\n        change position and size properties dynamically using\n          <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$paintedfieldproperties</span>. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"hqv1665702558806.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/hqv1665702558806.html\" title=\"Return or set the position and size for a specific instance of a field widget in a Form.\">$paintedfieldproperties</a> and <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"fhs1665702558897.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/fhs1665702558897.html\" title=\"For form components, you can override the layout as defined in the Define Frames worksheet using the $paintedfieldproperties ProcScript function. At runtime, the form displays the fields using the position and size coordinates and optional Z-order specified with this function.\">Changing Form Layout Dynamically</a>.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"swp1665702587155__section_hkd_vsh_5wb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1058569e208\">Lines</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"swp1665702587155__p_d100649e1_d100650e1_d100651e1\">A line is horizontal if its\n          <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Width</span> is greater than <code class=\"ph codeph\">1</code>, in which case, its\n          <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Height</span> must be <code class=\"ph codeph\">1</code>.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"swp1665702587155__p_d100652e1_d100653e1_d100654e1\">A line is vertical if its <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Width</span>\n        is greater than <code class=\"ph codeph\">1</code>, in which case, its <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Height</span> must be\n          <code class=\"ph codeph\">1</code>.</p>\n<div class=\"note note note_note\" id=\"swp1665702587155__note_yv2_wsh_5wb\"><span class=\"note__title\">Note:</span> The line itself has a width of 3 pixels, but the frame\n        required to draw the line is 1 character.</div>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_3615993\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_3615993\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Width (xsize) Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated März 15, 2023 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Width (xsize) Width of the object frame in the layout of a Form or Report, expressed in character cells, excluding the border (if present). xsize = Number Description The size of a character cell is determined by the Font0 , as defined in the usys.ini file. For more information, see Font0 . Applies To Component Entity Component Field Label Area Line Print Header Print Footer Break Frame Setting in ProcScript For component fields in forms, it is possible to change position and size properties dynamically using $paintedfieldproperties . For more information, see $paintedfieldproperties and Changing Form Layout Dynamically . Lines A line is horizontal if its Width is greater than 1 , in which case, its Height must be 1 . A line is vertical if its Width is greater than 1 , in which case, its Height must be 1 . Note: The line itself has a width of 3 pixels, but the frame required to draw the line is 1 character. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}